			<p>CryoLand offers a series of geospatial Snow and Land Ice Products with a pan-European, regional and local coverage:</p>
			<p><strong>Operational Snow Products:</strong>
				</p><ul>
					<li><u>Pan-European Snow Products:</u></li>
					<ul>
						<li>Fractional Snow Cover (FSC)<br>
						<ul>
							<li> «<u>daily_FSC_PanEuropean_Optical</u>»:<br>This near real time product from Optical Satellite data provides the daily Fractional Snow Cover with 0.005° x 0.005° (ca. 500 m x 500 m) pixel size for the Pan-European area, extending from 72°N / 11°W to 35°N / 50°E. Cloud covered pixels are masked over land.</li>
							<li> «<u>View_10day_FSC_PanEuropean_Cloudfree</u>» - a 10-day FSC Composite Cloudfree (Viewing Product):<br>This layer is a daily updated aggregated Fractional Snow Cover (FSC) map based on the most recent cloud free pixel information of the past 10 days of the daily pan-European FSC product. This layer is intended as a VIEWING service only.</li>
						</ul>
						</li>
						<li>Snow Water Equivalent (SWE; coarse resolution)<br>
							<ul>
								<li> «<u>daily_SWE_PanEuropean_Microwave</u>»:<br>The daily Pan-European Snow Water Equivalent (SWE) product is based on the combination of satellite-based microwave radiometer (DMSP SSM/I from 1987 – present) and ground-based weather station snow depth data provided by ECMWF. The product covers non-mountainous areas between 72°N/11°W and 35°N/50°E, with a pixel size of 0.10° x 0.10°. The  product is provided daily with 2 days delay  during the winter season, from the beginning of October until the end of July, through the CryoLand GeoPortal.</li>
								<li> «<u>avg_XXday_SSPI_PanEuropean_Microwave</u>»:<br>The SSPI (Standardized Snow Pack Index) provides information about the volume of the snowpack on a 10-day and a30-day basis relative to a reference period of 1979-2010. The relative snowpack volume is expressed as standardized values between -3 to 3. The SSPI is computed the same way as SPI (Standardized Precipitation Index), but it is based on the "daily PanEuropean Snow Water Equivalent (SWE)" product.</li>
							</ul>
						</li>
					</ul>

					<p>Both Products are generated daily in near real time.</p><p>

					</p><li><u>Regional Snow Products:</u></li>
					<ul>

						<li>Fractional Snow Cover Products (FSC) for Central Europe, Baltic Region and Scandinavia, generated with regionally adapted algorithms <br>
						<ul>
							<li> «<u>daily_FSC_Baltic_Optical</u>»:<br>Baltic The Fractional Snow Cover over the Baltic Area describes the snow-covered area, given as percentage (0-100%) of the land surface,  covered by snow with a spatial resolution of 500m. The underlying method uses a transmissivity map (a parameter describing the passage of light back and forth through forest canopy) enabling the estimation of areas covered by vegetation (trees and tall schrubs). The estimate is given with an uncertainty of 15% percentage points on a single pixel scale.</li>
							<li> «<u>daily_FSC_Alps_Optical</u>»:<br>This near real time product from Optical Satellite data provides the daily Fractional Snow Cover over the Alps and lowlands with 0.0025° x 0.0025° (ca. 250 m x 250 m) pixel size. Cloud covered pixels are masked.</li>
							<li> «<u>multitemp_FSC_Scandinavia_Optical</u>»:<br>Multi-temporal aggregated snow cover fraction (0-100%) for Scandinavia based on single-day snow maps. These maps are based on optical data from NASA's Terra MODIS sensor. Daily products are presented based on the latest available information. When regions are covered by clouds, we use older pixel up to 7 days. Service delivered from April-July.</li>
							<li> «<u>multitemp_FSC_Scandinavia_Optical_Radar</u>»:<br>Multi-sensor/temporal aggregated snow cover fraction (0-100%) for Scandinavia based on data from optical and radar sensor. Daily products are presented based on the latest available information. When regions are covered by clouds, we use older pixel up to 7 days. Wet snow from SAR is also used to estimate snow cover fraction. The products are based on data from NASA's Terra MODIS sensor and Radarsat-2. Service delivered from April-July.</li>
						</ul>
						</li>

						<li>Melting (wet) snow areas (SCAW) for Scandinavian mountain regions<br><ul><li> «<u>daily_SCAW_Scandinavia_Radar</u>»:<br>Detected wet snow from Radarsat-2. Each product shows regions of wet snow for the specific day of acquisition. The areas that are not wet can be covered by dry snow or are without snow. The spatial coverage varies from day to day depending on data availability. The service is delivered the during entire year.</li>
						</ul>
							</li>
							</ul>
					<li><u>In-situ:</u></li>
						<ul>
							<li> «<u>SYKE-Snow Stations</u>»:<br>In-situ observations of Fractional Snow cover at Finnish snow courses:&nbsp;&nbsp;one observation for each snow course represents an average value measured at 40-60 locations along a 2-4 km long transect through various landscapes. Location refers to central point of the course.</li>

						</ul>
				</ul>
