						<li> «<u>View_10day_LIE_Baltic_Cloudfree</u>» - a 10-day LIE Composite Cloudfree (Viewing Product):<br>This layer is a daily updated aggregated Lake Ice Extent (LIE) map based on the most recent cloud free pixel information of the past 10 days of the daily Baltic LIE product. This layer is intended as a VIEWING service only.</li>
						<li> «<u>LIE_Analysed_Lakes_Baltic</u>» - Areas ananlysed for Lake Ice occurrence:<br>The lake boundaries have been derived from GlobCover dataset (due.esrin.esa.int/globcover/), where a 250m buffer towards the interior of the lakes is used to exclude areas of shallow water and mixed pixels of water and land. The spatial resolution of the underlying satellite data (MODIS Terra) and the product is 250m.</li>
					</ul>
					</li>

					<li>River Ice Extent (RIE)<br>
					<ul>
						<li> «<u>RIE_SE_FI_Torne_River_2013_Radar</u>»:<br>Detected river ice using SAR (Terrasar-X and Radarsat-2). The product shows areas within a river stretch that is covered with ice. Each product is based on a single SAR scene and shows the ice coverage at the time of the satellite pass. The quality depends on the spatial resolution of the applied SAR mode. The service is delivered for selected rivers during the ice break up period. </li>
